  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of concealing the origin of illegally obtained money, typically by means of transfers involving foreign banks or legitimate businesses. Legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically include:\n\n1. Key elements:\n- Concealing the source of funds\n- Disguising the nature of illegal proceeds\n- Transforming illegal money into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Attempting to make illicit funds appear legal\n\n2. Common legal frameworks:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- International Financial Action Task Force (FATF) standards\n\n3. Typical criminal activities generating laundered funds:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Illegal gambling\n- Terrorist financing\n\n4. General stages of money laundering:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (complex financial transactions to obscure origin)\n- Integration (funds appear legitimate)\n\nFor specific legal details, I recommend consulting local legal professionals or official legal resources, as precise definitions can vary between jurisdictions.",
